1
00:00:57,599 --> 00:01:00,602
EPISODE 7

2
00:01:01,102 --> 00:01:02,645
PORK BELLY

3
00:01:20,872 --> 00:01:21,998
Thank you.

4
00:01:22,082 --> 00:01:23,249
-Thank you.
-Dad…

5
00:01:28,880 --> 00:01:29,881
Thank you.

6
00:02:17,053 --> 00:02:18,388
I'm going to take a walk.

7
00:02:18,972 --> 00:02:19,931
Okay.

8
00:02:30,316 --> 00:02:33,611
Your husband isn't in a rut
due to long years of marriage.

9
00:02:33,695 --> 00:02:35,155
He is cheating on you.

10
00:02:35,238 --> 00:02:37,574
Others can't possibly know
about other couples.

11
00:02:37,657 --> 00:02:40,410
It's harder to know
what's happening under your nose.

12
00:02:59,345 --> 00:03:00,430
Shall we go?

13
00:03:38,217 --> 00:03:39,260
Hello?

14
00:03:39,344 --> 00:03:41,429
Where are you? Are you there?

15
00:03:41,512 --> 00:03:42,847
Come inside the park.

16
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:11,751
Where did you spend the night?

17
00:04:12,627 --> 00:04:13,962
At a friend's house.

18
00:04:16,214 --> 00:04:17,924
Female or male?

19
00:04:19,133 --> 00:04:20,009
Why do you ask?

20
00:04:23,221 --> 00:04:25,515
I saw you at Gangnam Mart yesterday.

21
00:04:26,140 --> 00:04:27,642
Who was the woman in your car?

22
00:04:31,062 --> 00:04:33,022
Did you spend the night at her place?

23
00:04:37,777 --> 00:04:38,861
Dad.

24
00:04:39,904 --> 00:04:41,864
What will you do if Mom finds out?

25
00:04:41,948 --> 00:04:44,951
-She knows.
-She does?

26
00:04:50,540 --> 00:04:51,916
I have no excuse.

27
00:04:52,667 --> 00:04:54,460
I know I don't.

28
00:04:54,544 --> 00:04:56,504
But it can't be helped.

29
00:04:57,088 --> 00:04:58,506
You can't understand love--

30
00:05:01,509 --> 00:05:02,885
How?

31
00:05:04,887 --> 00:05:06,514
How could you, of all people?

32
00:05:08,057 --> 00:05:10,184
This isn't right.

33
00:05:12,020 --> 00:05:13,062
Who is she?

34
00:05:14,772 --> 00:05:16,190
No, I don't need to know.

35
00:05:17,025 --> 00:05:18,484
She's a piece of trash anyway.

36
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:44,677
Is Dad still asleep?

37
00:05:44,761 --> 00:05:46,888
He spent last night at a friend's.

38
00:05:47,472 --> 00:05:49,515
-Where's Hyang-gi?
-Exercising.

39
00:05:51,559 --> 00:05:52,894
Is this your love for me?

40
00:05:52,977 --> 00:05:54,103
Yes.

41
00:06:05,782 --> 00:06:07,658
I want to eat this again tomorrow.

42
00:06:07,742 --> 00:06:09,535
Sure. Do you like it?

43
00:06:10,244 --> 00:06:13,539
The number you have dialed
cannot be reached…

44
00:06:20,630 --> 00:06:23,424
Why is your phone off?
I was worried about you.

45
00:06:26,511 --> 00:06:27,887
I thought you were Hyang-gi.

46
00:06:27,970 --> 00:06:29,347
She didn't come home?

47
00:06:29,430 --> 00:06:31,224
She went for a walk.

48
00:06:31,891 --> 00:06:32,850
Have some breakfast.

49
00:06:36,187 --> 00:06:39,023
Hi, Dad. You're home early.

50
00:06:40,066 --> 00:06:41,192
Hey.

51
00:06:55,498 --> 00:06:58,751
I don't think I could ever get sick
of omurice.

52
00:06:58,835 --> 00:07:00,253
I'll make it often then.

53
00:07:07,385 --> 00:07:08,803
You should come eat.

54
00:07:13,182 --> 00:07:14,851
Hyang-gi found out.

55
00:07:17,353 --> 00:07:18,479
About what?

56
00:07:21,149 --> 00:07:22,400
You told her?

57
00:07:29,073 --> 00:07:31,200
Yesterday, I went to Gangnam Mart

58
00:07:31,284 --> 00:07:33,327
to buy some pork belly.

59
00:07:34,620 --> 00:07:36,747
That's when Hyang-gi saw us.

60
00:07:37,331 --> 00:07:39,333
You were grocery shopping with that woman?

61
00:07:39,417 --> 00:07:42,503
No, by myself. She was in the car.

62
00:07:44,172 --> 00:07:45,798
She saw us driving out.

63
00:07:48,134 --> 00:07:51,262
She called earlier in the morning
to ask me to meet her at Banpo Park.

64
00:07:51,888 --> 00:07:53,014
She confronted me.

65
00:07:54,515 --> 00:07:56,476
I told her the truth since she saw us.

66
00:07:59,353 --> 00:08:02,690
She was worried about you,
so I told her that you knew as well.

67
00:08:09,697 --> 00:08:11,949
Was the pork belly delicious?

68
00:08:20,750 --> 00:08:24,212
I'm sure she's fine.
She just doesn't want to see me.

69
00:08:25,922 --> 00:08:27,423
So you want to move out?

70
00:08:28,007 --> 00:08:29,383
No.

71
00:08:30,009 --> 00:08:30,927
Oh, dear.

72
00:08:37,517 --> 00:08:38,351
MY DAUGHTER

73
00:08:39,393 --> 00:08:40,770
Aren't you going to eat?

74
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:43,523
Coming.

75
00:08:48,861 --> 00:08:51,072
Did you guys fight?

76
00:08:51,656 --> 00:08:53,908
No, we were talking about Hyang-gi.

77
00:08:58,412 --> 00:09:00,915
-I'm worried about her.
-Don't be.

78
00:09:12,343 --> 00:09:13,678
Why aren't you eating?

79
00:09:13,761 --> 00:09:15,596
I was waiting for you.

80
00:09:17,181 --> 00:09:21,060
Ji-a, there's not a single thing
that you lack.

81
00:09:21,143 --> 00:09:22,228
You're polite and--

82
00:09:22,311 --> 00:09:26,023
Grandma, in Korea,
we say "there's not one thing" instead.

83
00:09:26,607 --> 00:09:27,650
That's what we say now.

84
00:09:27,733 --> 00:09:29,026
-"One thing"?
-Yes.

85
00:09:29,110 --> 00:09:30,528
Okay.

86
00:09:31,112 --> 00:09:33,614
I learned something new again
thanks to you.

87
00:09:35,783 --> 00:09:37,326
Why aren't you eating much?

88
00:09:37,410 --> 00:09:40,913
Well, I'll have some more later.

89
00:09:42,665 --> 00:09:44,041
I don't want to gain weight.

90
00:09:46,377 --> 00:09:47,962
It feels like a dream.

91
00:09:48,546 --> 00:09:51,132
That we're here? Or that I slept over?

92
00:09:51,215 --> 00:09:52,925
This moment.

93
00:09:56,053 --> 00:09:57,513
I can't

94
00:09:58,639 --> 00:10:02,810
come here alone for breakfast
looking all lonely.

95
00:10:03,352 --> 00:10:05,354
You're right. You'd be bored too.

96
00:10:07,023 --> 00:10:10,860
Ji-a, you're not a picky eater, are you?

97
00:10:10,943 --> 00:10:13,613
You brought a variety of food.
Even the potatoes.

98
00:10:13,696 --> 00:10:16,115
I love potato wedges.

99
00:10:22,997 --> 00:10:24,957
Have you been to Hanguk World before?

100
00:10:25,041 --> 00:10:28,836
I went twice with your mom and her sister
when they were young.

101
00:10:28,919 --> 00:10:31,505
The place has become even better.
You'd be in awe.

102
00:10:31,589 --> 00:10:32,757
Is that so?

103
00:10:33,841 --> 00:10:35,885
Why don't we go there?

104
00:10:35,968 --> 00:10:37,178
What about shopping?

105
00:10:37,261 --> 00:10:39,180
We can do that afterward.

106
00:10:43,434 --> 00:10:45,478
I'd like to meet your sister one day.

107
00:10:46,896 --> 00:10:50,149
You will see her soon

108
00:10:51,525 --> 00:10:53,194
once I die.

109
00:11:01,410 --> 00:11:03,204
That's a proper continental breakfast.

110
00:11:03,287 --> 00:11:05,915
You and I would do fine living abroad.

111
00:11:06,957 --> 00:11:08,042
That's true.

112
00:11:09,377 --> 00:11:12,797
Pi-young can't go a single day
without kimchi.

113
00:11:14,548 --> 00:11:16,884
Most Koreans are like that.

114
00:11:18,928 --> 00:11:19,929
Look at those twins.

115
00:11:23,391 --> 00:11:26,560
-Dad, is Hanguk World far?
-No.

116
00:11:26,644 --> 00:11:28,604
Gosh. Don't drop your food.

117
00:11:28,687 --> 00:11:30,648
-Focus on eating, okay?
-Okay.

118
00:11:32,483 --> 00:11:36,821
Do you remember how you took me
to Hanguk World when I was little?

119
00:11:36,904 --> 00:11:39,657
-I remember.
-I had a blast.

120
00:11:40,408 --> 00:11:42,743
It wasn't that fun
when our kindergarten class went.

121
00:11:46,997 --> 00:11:49,083
Did you ever go there again?

122
00:11:49,792 --> 00:11:51,001
No.

123
00:11:51,085 --> 00:11:52,336
Let's go today.

124
00:11:54,171 --> 00:11:56,924
-Well…
-Let's see how much it has changed.

125
00:11:58,384 --> 00:11:59,677
Let's go.

126
00:12:00,428 --> 00:12:03,681
Let's enjoy other people's company
and forget about everything.

127
00:12:04,432 --> 00:12:06,684
Thank you. Let's go.

128
00:12:07,560 --> 00:12:08,769
Goodness.

129
00:12:10,688 --> 00:12:13,190
-Gosh.
-This is amazing.

130
00:12:19,071 --> 00:12:20,281
Goodness.

131
00:12:20,364 --> 00:12:22,783
They just got dressed up. It's a costume.

132
00:12:22,867 --> 00:12:25,453
-Why don't we do it too?
-I'm good.

133
00:12:25,536 --> 00:12:27,580
There are many pretty ones too, you know?

134
00:12:27,663 --> 00:12:28,747
Really?

135
00:12:28,831 --> 00:12:31,292
Yes. Come on, let's go.

136
00:12:31,375 --> 00:12:32,668
This is it.

137
00:12:35,838 --> 00:12:37,631
They look wonderful.

138
00:12:37,715 --> 00:12:39,467
-Don't they look pretty?
-Yes.

139
00:12:39,550 --> 00:12:40,718
Let's go inside.

140
00:12:45,264 --> 00:12:46,182
Hello, Father.

141
00:12:46,265 --> 00:12:47,516
Are you home?

142
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:50,227
No, I'm at work for recording.

143
00:12:50,311 --> 00:12:51,645
When will you be done?

144
00:12:51,729 --> 00:12:55,608
I came to Seoul to buy you
some good herbal medicine.

145
00:12:56,567 --> 00:12:57,902
I wanted to see you too.

146
00:12:57,985 --> 00:12:59,612
I don't like herbal medicine.

147
00:12:59,695 --> 00:13:02,656
You should still take them.

148
00:13:02,740 --> 00:13:04,992
Your body needs to stay warm
if you want a baby.

149
00:13:05,618 --> 00:13:06,619
What about in an hour?

150
00:13:07,286 --> 00:13:10,498
No. I'll just take them
when I feel better.

151
00:13:10,581 --> 00:13:13,000
All right, then. Goodbye.

152
00:13:14,627 --> 00:13:16,712
-Mr. Kim.
-Yes, Mr. Chairman?

153
00:13:16,795 --> 00:13:18,380
Don't address me like that.

154
00:13:19,798 --> 00:13:20,883
How's your condition?

155
00:13:20,966 --> 00:13:22,676
I'm always doing great.

156
00:13:22,760 --> 00:13:24,762
It's all thanks to you.

157
00:13:24,845 --> 00:13:27,348
-Are you doing fine in bed?
-I am.

158
00:13:27,932 --> 00:13:30,684
-How about you?
-I'd give myself a B plus.

159
00:13:31,602 --> 00:13:33,395
I have aged, you know?

160
00:13:34,188 --> 00:13:35,022
I see.

161
00:13:38,192 --> 00:13:41,362
I wonder how the original Dong-mi
is doing.

162
00:13:41,445 --> 00:13:42,738
She hasn't contacted me.

163
00:13:57,294 --> 00:14:00,381
Everything has changed.

164
00:14:00,464 --> 00:14:01,924
You're right.

165
00:14:12,226 --> 00:14:13,185
Let's go.

166
00:14:17,481 --> 00:14:19,567
Yes. This is it.

167
00:14:20,067 --> 00:14:21,694
Take your pick.

168
00:14:29,493 --> 00:14:31,036
Can you ride that?

169
00:14:31,120 --> 00:14:34,039
Of course not. But you should.
I'll take photos.

170
00:14:34,123 --> 00:14:35,374
Okay.

171
00:14:35,457 --> 00:14:38,377
They're screaming.
Will you really be okay?

172
00:14:38,460 --> 00:14:39,920
I always sit in the very back.

173
00:14:47,845 --> 00:14:49,513
Ji-a!

174
00:15:08,616 --> 00:15:12,119
We definitely click.
We look great together.

175
00:15:12,202 --> 00:15:14,538
I shouldn't laugh.

176
00:15:15,164 --> 00:15:16,540
It's okay.

177
00:15:17,124 --> 00:15:19,877
Oh, dear. This is driving me crazy.

178
00:15:20,586 --> 00:15:21,670
Let's go.

179
00:15:24,798 --> 00:15:26,592
That's terrifying.

180
00:15:28,677 --> 00:15:33,015
Goodness. It feels like
it's flying toward me.

181
00:15:46,445 --> 00:15:47,446
Doors opening.

182
00:15:49,823 --> 00:15:51,951
-Hello.
-Hello.

183
00:15:57,373 --> 00:15:59,124
Do you have any pets?

184
00:15:59,208 --> 00:16:00,376
No.

185
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:02,753
Do you not like furry animals?

186
00:16:02,836 --> 00:16:06,340
I do. I just choose not to have one.
I can't.

187
00:16:06,423 --> 00:16:07,883
You must be allergic.

188
00:16:07,967 --> 00:16:09,218
I'd feel sorry

189
00:16:10,302 --> 00:16:11,845
leaving them home all day.

190
00:16:12,763 --> 00:16:14,139
It's not right.

191
00:16:17,017 --> 00:16:18,686
Is Hyang-gi still not home?

192
00:16:20,688 --> 00:16:21,772
Okay.

193
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:29,655
Hello.

194
00:16:49,675 --> 00:16:50,801
What?

195
00:16:56,515 --> 00:16:57,975
Hello?

196
00:16:58,058 --> 00:16:59,351
Hello, madam.

197
00:16:59,435 --> 00:17:02,980
Don't call me that.
We've known each other for years.

198
00:17:04,023 --> 00:17:05,107
Are you well?

199
00:17:05,190 --> 00:17:07,484
Yes, I am. But…

200
00:17:07,568 --> 00:17:09,403
Did my husband

201
00:17:10,237 --> 00:17:13,115
ask you to concoct some herbal medicine?

202
00:17:14,158 --> 00:17:14,992
No.

203
00:17:15,075 --> 00:17:18,287
He's such a softhearted and nosy man.

204
00:17:18,370 --> 00:17:22,499
He always sends herbal medicine
to people around him if they seem unwell.

205
00:17:22,583 --> 00:17:26,003
I see. That must be why
he's still so successful.

206
00:17:26,086 --> 00:17:29,506
Oh, please. Anyway, all right then.

207
00:17:29,590 --> 00:17:31,216
Okay. Goodbye.

208
00:17:31,967 --> 00:17:33,010
Bye.

209
00:17:42,936 --> 00:17:45,647
Goodness. Let's go now.

210
00:17:45,731 --> 00:17:48,025
-We should go shopping.
-Okay.

211
00:17:48,108 --> 00:17:51,403
-Did you have fun today?
-Yes. It was terrific.

212
00:17:52,196 --> 00:17:54,948
Thanks to you, I had a blast as well.

213
00:17:57,951 --> 00:17:59,078
Let's take a selfie.

214
00:17:59,161 --> 00:18:00,871
One, two, three.

215
00:18:08,962 --> 00:18:10,714
-Grandma, over there.
-Yes?

216
00:18:10,798 --> 00:18:12,841
-Sure.
-Let's go.

217
00:18:19,264 --> 00:18:22,601
Grandma, she looks terrifying.

218
00:18:28,023 --> 00:18:32,111
"My girlfriend's puppy had died.
She was completely heartbroken.

219
00:18:32,194 --> 00:18:33,654
So I gave her mine.

220
00:18:34,321 --> 00:18:37,491
My dog is an intelligent black poodle.

221
00:18:37,574 --> 00:18:41,203
-Doesn't her face look pallid?
-Thankfully, my girlfriend got over it.

222
00:18:41,286 --> 00:18:44,331
-She does look unwell.
-We fought over something trivial one day,

223
00:18:44,414 --> 00:18:46,583
refused to reconcile,
and broke up instead."

224
00:18:46,667 --> 00:18:48,168
Goodness.

225
00:18:48,252 --> 00:18:50,754
"How do I get my dog back?

226
00:18:50,838 --> 00:18:53,090
I feel heartless doing so

227
00:18:53,173 --> 00:18:55,717
since she just got over the loss
of her puppy.

228
00:18:56,260 --> 00:18:59,346
But I miss my dog terribly.

229
00:18:59,429 --> 00:19:01,390
Please give me some advice."

230
00:19:03,851 --> 00:19:06,770
Doctor, please share your thoughts.

231
00:19:06,854 --> 00:19:08,939
He must be in a serious dilemma.

232
00:19:09,022 --> 00:19:10,774
Do you have a dog?

233
00:19:10,858 --> 00:19:13,527
Yes, I have two.

234
00:19:13,610 --> 00:19:16,864
What's important is determining

235
00:19:16,947 --> 00:19:19,449
whether his dog is happy living with her.

236
00:19:19,533 --> 00:19:23,036
Judging by the story, she seems to be
taking good care of the dog.

237
00:19:23,120 --> 00:19:25,581
So I think it's doing well.

238
00:19:25,664 --> 00:19:29,376
While they were still dating,
his dog was probably doing well

239
00:19:29,459 --> 00:19:31,628
-since he'd visit often.
-What would you do?

240
00:19:32,212 --> 00:19:35,549
I should bring the dog back
and get her a new dog.

241
00:19:35,632 --> 00:19:39,052
-Dogs can get stressed too.
-Exactly.

242
00:19:39,136 --> 00:19:43,098
That's what you should do for the dog.
But in the girlfriend's case,

243
00:19:43,182 --> 00:19:47,311
her ex-boyfriend she used to love

244
00:19:47,394 --> 00:19:49,354
is asking for his dog back.

245
00:19:49,438 --> 00:19:53,192
That'll only taint all the good memories
they had together.

246
00:19:53,275 --> 00:19:56,862
She'll think, "Is this
what the man I loved is really like?"

247
00:19:56,945 --> 00:20:00,449
It would be impossible
not to think that way.

248
00:20:01,992 --> 00:20:03,160
You're right.

249
00:20:03,243 --> 00:20:07,706
In my opinion, you should let her
keep your dog.

250
00:20:08,498 --> 00:20:12,336
Also, your ex-girlfriend will think of you

251
00:20:12,419 --> 00:20:16,715
every now and then
while taking care of your dog.

252
00:20:16,798 --> 00:20:17,716
Right.

253
00:20:18,342 --> 00:20:21,428
-She may even call you one day.
-That's true.

254
00:20:21,511 --> 00:20:22,804
A breakup is a breakup.

255
00:20:24,181 --> 00:20:27,309
Many couples break up because they refuse
to swallow their pride.

256
00:20:27,392 --> 00:20:30,437
-And refuse to call as well.
-That's right.

257
00:20:30,520 --> 00:20:34,483
She may call him if his dog is sick
or not doing too well.

258
00:20:34,566 --> 00:20:35,859
That could be her excuse.

259
00:20:35,943 --> 00:20:39,029
Exactly. They might be able
to get back together.

260
00:20:40,280 --> 00:20:42,074
I hope we were of help.

261
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:45,619
"Swing of the Dog" by Caleb.

